- Site visit scheduled for Tuesday, 14th (pending confirmation)  
- Lagos Logistics to provide warehouse access documents by Wednesday  
- Joint team meeting set for Thursday, 16th at 10 a.m.  
- Your team to lead coordination with local vendors  
Add a line at the end: ‘Please let me know if any adjustments are needed before Friday.’ It shows diligence and respect for his time."
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "And what about a small gift? I’ve been thinking of bringing a box of Ota tea when I visit next week—just as a token of appreciation. Is that okay?"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That’s thoughtful—but wait until after the initial follow-up, maybe during your next visit. A gift right after the meeting might seem too eager. But a modest, tasteful item like a box of premium Nigerian tea or a locally made notebook with a simple note—‘Thank you for the opportunity to collaborate’—delivered a few days later is perfectly appropriate. Just make sure it’s not flashy or expensive. The gesture should reflect gratitude, not obligation."
    }
  ]
